nts_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"Hello.\n\nA few days ago, I was looking at Roblox subdomains, and I noticed an unusual one called creatorforum.roblox.com. Upon further investigation, I visited it and saw that creatorforum.roblox.com's CNAME was a nonexistant Discourse website.\n I immediately reported to info@roblox.com, and eventually talked to Antek Baranski on the bugbounty@roblox.com email address. The issue has been fixed since reporting, but I was told to send a report here.\n\nIf I had a Discourse account, I could've taken over the CNAME for creatorforum.roblox.com and then it would've been a full subdomain takeover on that subdomain.\n\nAs mentioned earlier in the report, the issue has been resolved and as you can see the subdomain creatorforum.roblox.com no longer exists.\n\n\nThanks,\nJack","bounty_amount":"1000.0","formatted_bounty":"$1,000","weakness":{"id":75,"name":"Privilege Escalation"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2020-03-24T19:57:36.552Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-48882960.51900685,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":79,"voters":["spam404","ali","realtess","powerjacobb1","pikayrachu","dmc3","nice_going","jackb898","smelt","navprak","and 69 more..."],"severity":{"rating":"high","author_type":"Team"},"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"activities":[{"id":1964755,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Sorry, I didn't mention the problems with having a subdomain takeover. Obviously as you know subdomain takeovers are a very critical vulnerability, and for a few distinct reasons.\n\nSubdomain takeovers allow you to upload any content to the taken over CNAME, and that content will be shown on creatorforum.roblox.com. This allows extreme phishing, because everyone trusts the .roblox.com domain name. 